Ugh.  I lived in the San Luis Valley for two years, not far (in Colorado terms!) from both the town of San Luis and the New Mexico border.  My house had clear close views of Blanca Peak, Ute Mountain, the San Juans and the Sangres.  Thanks for the memories, nice to see the area again, but this is the worst-constructed documentary of all time.  &#34;Docu-drama&#34; would be a better fit, with waaaaay too much drama.  Better you should read about the &#34;Mysterious Valley&#34; in the series of the same name, written by Christopher O'Brien.  Maybe someday he'll produce a genuine doc.  Hope so, can't wait.
